{
  "texts": [
    "The majority of studies, accounting for 52%, focus on the Development step in DevOps.",
    "In this step, AI-driven security approaches can directly assist software developers by detecting vulnerabilities in their source code, providing explanations, and suggesting repairs.",
    "Following this, 24% of the studies concentrate on the Operation and Monitoring step in DevOps.",
    "During this phase, AI-driven security approaches can learn from historical data and help monitor and detect anomalies occurring in software systems.",
    "Additionally, 17% of studies focus on developing AI-driven approaches for securing the Code Commit step in DevOps, while the remaining 7% concentrate on the Build, Test, and Deployment step in DevOps.During the full-text review, we conducted data extraction to gather all relevant information necessary for a comprehensive and insightful response to our two research questions outlined in Section 3.1."
  ]
}